'''Heel Lifts are wedge type Shoe Inserts that affix inside any footwear to make the user look taller.'''

They are manufactured using Eva Resin foam and are also called  shoe lifts in North America.

They are used in all walks of life by men and women who wish to appear taller,look slimmer to others,or to correct a limb length discrepency in one foot.


The term 'Heel Lifts' has become common in describing secret height increasing shoe lifts.
[http://www.celebheights.com]
[http://www.shoelifts.co.uk]
They typically come in sizes ranging from 0.25 to 3 inches. Users of larger sizes obviously need top use high topped type footwear to allow the secret height increasing insert to fit comfortably inside th users footwear.

Research shows that approx 5 million people on a daily basis wear Shoe Inserts in their footwear to appear taller.
[http://www.shoelifts.co.uk]

The origion of the term 'Heel Lifts' can be attributed to the fact that the user 'inserts' an external structure inside the interior of the footwear in the heel area,thus lifting the wearers heel in the process.
[http://www.shoelifts.co.uk]


Heel Lifts are also used for limb length discrepency issues.